{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.39",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 39,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 39",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 39 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:1",
      "text": "“ Do you know the time when the mountain goats give birth? Do you watch when the doe bears fawns?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:2",
      "text": "Can you count the months that they fulfill? Or do you know the time when they give birth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:3",
      "text": "They bow themselves. They bear their young. They end their labor pains.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:4",
      "text": "Their young ones become strong. They grow up in the open field. They go out, and don’t return again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:5",
      "text": "“ Who has set the wild donkey free? Or who has loosened the bonds of the swift donkey,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:6",
      "text": "whose home I have made the wilderness, and the salt land his dwelling place?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:7",
      "text": "He scorns the tumult of the city, neither does he hear the shouting of the driver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:8",
      "text": "The range of the mountains is his pasture. He searches after every green thing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:9",
      "text": "“ Will the wild ox be content to serve you? Or will he stay by your feeding trough?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:10",
      "text": "Can you hold the wild ox in the furrow with his harness? Or will he till the valleys after you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:11",
      "text": "Will you trust him, because his strength is great? Or will you leave to him your labor?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:12",
      "text": "Will you confide in him, that he will bring home your seed, and gather the grain of your threshing floor?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:13",
      "text": "“The wings of the ostrich wave proudly, but are they the feathers and plumage of love?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:14",
      "text": "For she leaves her eggs on the earth, warms them in the dust,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:15",
      "text": "and forgets that the foot may crush them, or that the wild animal may trample them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:16",
      "text": "She deals harshly with her young ones, as if they were not hers. Though her labor is in vain, she is without fear,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:17",
      "text": "because God has deprived her of wisdom, neither has he imparted to her understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:18",
      "text": "When she lifts up herself on high, she scorns the horse and his rider.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:19",
      "text": "“ Have you given the horse might? Have you clothed his neck with a quivering mane?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:20",
      "text": "Have you made him to leap as a locust? The glory of his snorting is awesome.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:21",
      "text": "He paws in the valley, and rejoices in his strength. He goes out to meet the armed men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:22",
      "text": "He mocks at fear, and is not dismayed, neither does he turn back from the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:23",
      "text": "The quiver rattles against him, the flashing spear and the javelin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:24",
      "text": "He eats up the ground with fierceness and rage, neither does he stand still at the sound of the trumpet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:25",
      "text": "As often as the trumpet sounds he snorts, ‘ Aha!’ He smells the battle afar off, the thunder of the captains, and the shouting.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:26",
      "text": "“ Is it by your wisdom that the hawk soars, and stretches her wings toward the south?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:27",
      "text": "Is it at your command that the eagle mounts up, and makes his nest on high?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:28",
      "text": "On the cliff he dwells and makes his home, on the point of the cliff and the stronghold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:29",
      "text": "From there he spies out the prey. His eyes see it afar off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.39.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:30",
      "text": "His young ones also suck up blood. Where the slain are, there he is.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
